<title type="html"><![CDATA[CopyNES Settings, What are yours?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1674&amp;p=14318#p14318"><![CDATA[
I've used CopyNES with a few different boards, all running XP SP2, always using 0378h for the address, no IRQ (BIOS often has set at 7, but always disabled in Windows, it should be irrelevant anyways), but mode has always been different:<br /><br />A7V8X - EPP 1.9<br />K8N-E Deluxe - EPP + ECP (some sort of combo mode)<br />K8N-VM - Bi-directional<br /><br />These might not be the only configs that work for me, but once I would find one that worked I didn't mess with them any further.<br /><br />I also tried it on a Win98 machine, can't remember the board, it was ASUS PIII board, that one worked with EPP, there was not a setting for EPP version.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=158">BootGod</a> — Tue Jun 20, 2006 4:46 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
